description:
You are a Solar Energy Systems Engineer evaluating a concentrating solar power (CSP) project. Using PySAM, create a molten salt power tower (MSPT) model with a net power block capacity of 100 MW, 10 hours of thermal energy storage, and a solar multiple of 2.4. Use a high-DNI TMY weather file from the US Southwest (such as Tucson, Phoenix, or Daggett) found in the solar resource directory path listed in /home/ga/.SAM/solar_resource_dir.txt.

Extract the annual energy (kWh), capacity factor (%), and real LCOE (cents/kWh) from the model. Save the Python script used to /home/ga/Documents/SAM_Projects/csp_power_tower_model.py and export the results to /home/ga/Documents/SAM_Projects/csp_power_tower_results.json using the following structure:

{
  "project_name": "MSPT_100MW_10hrTES",
  "weather_file": "<path to weather file used>",
  "configuration": {
    "P_ref_mw": 100,
    "tshours": 10,
    "solar_multiple": 2.4
  },
  "results": {
    "annual_energy_kwh": <value>,
    "annual_energy_gwh": <value divided by 1e6>,
    "capacity_factor_pct": <value>,
    "lcoe_real_cents_per_kwh": <value>
  }
}
